The paper deals with the problem of downlink multicell processing with finite backhaul capacity, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the use of multiple access diamond channel and Gaussian interference channel, which are common in network information theory (cs.NI). The paper may also be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) due to the use of Gaussian interference channel. Finally, the paper may be related to game theory (cs.GT) as it involves the study of upper bounds and the reduction of gaps between upper bounds and achievable schemes.
